The paper deals with distance oracles for planar graphs, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG) and data structures (cs.DS). The use of failing vertices also suggests a connection to fault-tolerant computing, which falls under the category of numerical analysis (cs.NA). The paper also involves analyzing the size and query time of the oracles, which could be considered a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) or graph theory (cs.GT).
